snippet.textDisplay:
Ethan: When Spencer pauses he is thinking, do not interrupt; he is what is called dissociating [when eyes glaze over a bit and they don't move but are not scared or stressed in position], it can be hard to read with a personality and brainpower like his, but he will think until he either understands the concept or is confused; if he is confused he will try again or walk away if he understands he will attempt to do it tentatively and when that happens any minor movement toward the action you want is a triumph [say yes and treat...wait...give command...say yes with action and treat...do this about 5 times...then say yes without treat so he will do the action "harder" to get the treat]; he will get it.

Mark: no tips needed, she reacts well to how you teach and you read her well and know if she gets something or doesn't. She is very consistent with her behaviours and very expressive in the face so it is easier to understand her.
